# API consumption (Marham frontend)

HTTP APIs live in **this Next.js app** at `app/api/` (Drizzle ORM + MySQL). The frontend calls them via `lib/client/*` using `NEXT_PUBLIC_MARHAM_API_URL` (defaults to `http://localhost:3001`).

## Adding a new endpoint

1. Add Zod schema in `lib/schemas/`
2. Add query functions in `lib/db/queries/`
3. Add plain async function in `lib/services/`
4. Add thin Route Handler in `app/api/` (`export const runtime = "nodejs"`)
5. Add path to `lib/constants/marham-api-endpoints.ts`
6. Add typed fetch helper in `lib/client/` (for client components only)

## Examples

```tsx
// ✅ Server Component — direct import (no HTTP round-trip)
import { getDoctorsListingPageData } from "@/lib/services/doctors-listing-page"

const { doctors, meta } = await getDoctorsListingPageData(filters)

// ✅ Client Component — lib helper calling local API
import { fetchDoctorsListing } from "@/lib/client/doctors-listing-service"

const { doctors, meta } = await fetchDoctorsListing({ page: currentPage + 1 })
```

```ts
// ✅ Route handler pattern
import { parseSearchParams } from "@/lib/schemas/parse"
import { getDoctorsSchema } from "@/lib/schemas/doctors"
import { getDoctorListing } from "@/lib/services/doctors"
import { handleApiError, jsonSuccess } from "@/lib/api/handle-api"

const query = parseSearchParams(getDoctorsSchema, searchParams)
const data = await getDoctorListing(query)
return jsonSuccess(data)
```

## Env

- `NEXT_PUBLIC_MARHAM_API_URL` — API base URL (e.g. `http://localhost:3001`)
- `DB_*`, `DB_POOL_SIZE`, `MARHAM_URL`, CDN vars — server-only in `.env` (never `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` for secrets)

## Legacy

`MarhamOne/` (NestJS on :3000) is reference only; do not add new endpoints there for this frontend.
